      "text": "Casey Gollan: Oh yeah! And the third special guest is my ghost. I started to think about my ghost. There is a version of me, and I think there probably will be a version of everyone, that never leaves Oxbow. I was trying to reconnect with myself from 10 years ago and understand. So, my ghost is here. Sitting there. Came to my talk and has been having the same existential thoughts for 10 years while I've gotten the chance to move through and do other stuff. I thought it's nice that my ghost is here. It's really hard to talk to yourself from 10 years ago. I started to think: what would I want to hear from myself at 35? And I was like...I kind of might not? Or like if I could talk to death — or something? — and know how I'm going to die? I might not want to know. It made me think a lot about like what that means. The time relationships here are really interesting. \n"
